  "body": "# Problem\nWhen a dapp requests permission to connect to an account (address) a permission dialog is shown. The selected account looks tappable, giving the impression that the account can be changed here (e.g. a account selector bottom sheet will come up).\n\nThis is currently not possible. \n\n## Implementation\nChange the color of the account name to black to make it appear less tappable. \nColor: Black\nFont: Inter medium\nFont-size: 13\nSee [Figma](https://www.figma.com/file/MYWmd1buvc2AMvUmFP9w42t5/Browser?node-id=3000%3A5095)\n\n![Frame 3](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/35233054/76215541-43d0a480-620f-11ea-8396-669c153a8906.png)\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\nColor of account name in permission dialog is black\n\n## Notes\nInvestigate if/how account can be changed after dapp has send request to client and before address has been shared.\n\n## Future Steps\n\n- Allow 'connect' as after dapp request to connect\n- In long-term pipeline: allow burner account for dapps",
